<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="180" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="57" pageNumber="180">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="57" pageNumber="180">
This taxon is a distinctive species which seems to be restricted to chalky limestone flats usually occurring as a dense carpet on clay-like soils in open savannahs; known from North America and Central America (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027794" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="1 - 109" refId="B25" refString="Peterson, PM, Annable, CR, 1991. Systematics of the annual species of Muhlenbergia (Poaceae - Eragrostideae). Systematic Botany Monographs 31: 1 - 109, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25027794" title="Systematics of the annual species of Muhlenbergia (Poaceae - Eragrostideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027794" volume="31" year="1991">Peterson and Annable 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brako, L" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="57" pageNumber="180" pagination="1 - 1286" refId="B2" refString="Brako, L, Zarucchi, JL, 1993. Catalogue of the flowering plants and gymnosperms of Peru. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 45: 1 - 1286" title="Catalogue of the flowering plants and gymnosperms of Peru." volume="45" year="1993">Brako and Zarucchi 1993</bibRefCitation>
). Although previously included for Peru in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hitchcock, AS" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="291 - 556" refId="B16" refString="Hitchcock, AS, 1927. The grasses of Ecuador, Peru, and Bolivia. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 24: 291 - 556" title="The grasses of Ecuador, Peru, and Bolivia." volume="24" year="1927">Hitchcock (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Standley, PC" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Systematics and Evolution" pageId="60" pageNumber="183" refId="B57" refString="Standley, PC, 1936. Gramineae. In: Macbride JF (Ed.) Flora of Peru. Publications of the Field Museum of Natural History, Botanical Series 13: 96-261." title="Gramineae. In: Macbride JF (Ed.) Flora of Peru. Publications of the Field Museum of Natural History, Botanical Series 13: 96 - 261." year="1936">Standley (1936)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Tovar, O" journalOrPublisher="Ruizia" pageId="60" pageNumber="183" pagination="1 - 480" refId="B59" refString="Tovar, O, 1993. Las Gramineas (Poaceae) del Peru. Ruizia 13: 1 - 480" title="Las Gramineas (Poaceae) del Peru." volume="13" year="1993">Tovar (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, the specimens cited are 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. ciliata" order="Poales" pageId="57" pageNumber="180" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="ciliata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="180">M. ciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without prominent cilia along the lateral veins (see discussion of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. ciliata" order="Poales" pageId="57" pageNumber="180" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="ciliata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="180">M. ciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
